In a 2 1/2 quart saucepan, heat olive oil and saute onions until golden, about 5 minutes. Whisk in flour, salt, Italian seasoning and pepper. Cook until flour is absorbed, about 2-5 minutes. Slowly add LACTAID(R) Fat Free Milk and tomatoes, stirring constantly, heat just to boiling. Simmer for 5 minutes and serve warm.